1
00:03:27,613 --> 00:03:30,613
It all started on the day that I died.

2
00:03:30,613 --> 00:03:32,524
If there had been an obituary...

3
00:03:33,013 --> 00:03:35,891
...it would've described
the unremarkable life...

4
00:03:36,013 --> 00:03:38,402
... of an unremarkable woman...

5
00:03:38,413 --> 00:03:40,563
... survived by no one.

6
00:03:40,813 --> 00:03:42,405
But there was no obituary...

7
00:03:42,613 --> 00:03:44,729
... because the day that I died...

8
00:03:45,013 --> 00:03:48,892
... was also the day I started to live.

9
00:03:49,213 --> 00:03:51,010
But that comes later.

10
00:04:02,413 --> 00:04:03,613
This was my life.

11
00:04:03,613 --> 00:04:06,605
Days blended together,
consistently ordinary...

12
00:04:06,613 --> 00:04:10,003
... thanks to a job that was the practical
version of my passion.

13
00:04:10,213 --> 00:04:12,283
-I'm sorry.
-Watch where you' re going!

14
00:04:12,613 --> 00:04:14,968
I was supposed to be an artist by now.

15
00:04:15,013 --> 00:04:16,241
Instead...

16
00:04:16,813 --> 00:04:19,930
...I was designing ads for beauty cream.

17
00:04:23,413 --> 00:04:27,013
-You are so addicted to that stuff, Sally.
-Happily.

18
00:04:27,013 --> 00:04:29,846
-Beau-line is magic in a bottle.
-I don't know how you get it.

19
00:04:30,013 --> 00:04:32,766
-It's not even in production yet.
-We have our ways.

20
00:04:34,813 --> 00:04:36,371
-Hey.
-No!

21
00:04:39,013 --> 00:04:41,925
Headaches again.
My brain's all tight and cranky.

22
00:04:42,613 --> 00:04:46,813
In one week, precisely, we will Iaunch
the most exciting...

23
00:04:46,813 --> 00:04:49,771
...and revolutionary product
to hit the beauty industry since...

24
00:04:51,013 --> 00:04:52,412
...soap.

25
00:04:53,413 --> 00:04:54,926
Beau-line.

26
00:04:56,413 --> 00:04:59,530
Now, Beau-line doesn't
just hide the effects of aging...

27
00:05:00,013 --> 00:05:01,526
...it actually reverses them.

28
00:05:01,813 --> 00:05:03,610
However, with change...

29
00:05:04,213 --> 00:05:06,124
...must come sacrifice.

30
00:05:06,613 --> 00:05:08,251
My husband...

31
00:05:08,413 --> 00:05:12,613
...and I have decided that
it's time for me to step aside...

32
00:05:12,613 --> 00:05:14,205
...as the face of Hedare.

33
00:05:14,413 --> 00:05:17,371
It has been a magnificent 15 years.

34
00:05:18,013 --> 00:05:22,213
But we have decided to choose
a new face to represent Beau-Iine.

35
00:05:22,213 --> 00:05:23,612
Exactly.

36
00:05:24,613 --> 00:05:26,126
Drina.

37
00:05:26,413 --> 00:05:28,290
The future of Hedare Beauty.

38
00:05:30,013 --> 00:05:32,402
And now, ladies and gentlemen,
I look forward...

39
00:05:33,013 --> 00:05:37,086
...to seeing you at the gala, where you
can toast to Drina and our success.

40
00:05:37,213 --> 00:05:40,444
Careful, George.
She's not old enough to drink.

41
00:05:45,613 --> 00:05:49,447
You've got more talent than anybody
in the building, which I hate you for.

42
00:05:49,813 --> 00:05:54,013
Sal, this is my first lead campaign.
It's gotta be perfect. You know that.

43
00:05:54,013 --> 00:05:56,402
What is wrong with you?!

44
00:05:58,213 --> 00:05:59,441
Good luck.

45
00:06:00,613 --> 00:06:01,966
Yeah.

46
00:06:02,413 --> 00:06:04,973
You simply couldn't resist it, could you?

47
00:06:05,413 --> 00:06:08,325
You had to make
a scene out of it, Laurel.

48
00:06:08,413 --> 00:06:09,613
What's the matter, George?

49
00:06:09,613 --> 00:06:11,444
Did I steal your moment?

50
00:06:12,613 --> 00:06:14,171
Come in!

51
00:06:29,413 --> 00:06:30,971
Hi, Mr. Hedare.

52
00:06:32,413 --> 00:06:34,449
Did you still want to see me, or...?

53
00:06:34,813 --> 00:06:37,566
-Sit.
-Right. Okay.

54
00:06:42,013 --> 00:06:43,651
I'm not pleased.

55
00:06:46,213 --> 00:06:49,444
This isn't even close to what I wanted.

56
00:06:49,813 --> 00:06:52,008
I can't imagine what on earth
you were thinking.

57
00:06:52,213 --> 00:06:53,362
I am so sorry--

58
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:56,803
I mean, look at this red. It's all wrong.
I wanted it darker.

59
00:06:57,013 --> 00:07:01,723
-I specifically heard you say--
-I know what I said.

60
00:07:02,413 --> 00:07:04,813
-Okay. Maybe I misunderstood you.
-Clearly.

61
00:07:04,813 --> 00:07:06,690
Mr. Hedare, I know I can fix it.

62
00:07:07,213 --> 00:07:09,329
If you give me a chance,
I know I can fix it.

63
00:07:09,613 --> 00:07:11,922
I do not reward incompetence.

64
00:07:12,013 --> 00:07:17,212
I have no idea why I expected your art
to show better taste than your wardrobe.

65
00:07:17,413 --> 00:07:20,325
Oh, and do try and get
a manicure, will you?

66
00:07:20,413 --> 00:07:22,563
Oh, for God's sake, George.

67
00:07:24,013 --> 00:07:25,213
Let her fix it.

68
00:07:25,213 --> 00:07:26,965
She's good and you know it.

69
00:07:28,813 --> 00:07:30,013
Whatever.

70
00:07:30,013 --> 00:07:31,571
By tomorrow night.

71
00:07:32,413 --> 00:07:33,687
Midnight.

72
00:07:34,213 --> 00:07:35,965
Right. Thank you.

73
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,371
Excuse me. Hi!

74
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:28,365
Do you think you could just
maybe turn the music down...

75
00:08:29,533 --> 00:08:31,364
...just a little bit?

76
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,491
No? Okay.

77
00:09:21,133 --> 00:09:23,203
Kitty! Kitty.

78
00:09:23,533 --> 00:09:26,605
How'd you get up there?
Come down here.

79
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:30,810
What, are you stuck?

80
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:35,928
You're gonna make me come out there.

81
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,893
Hey! Easy! Hold on a minute!
Wait! Wait! Wait!

82
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:12,133
Whatever you're thinking or feeling...

83
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:15,133
...it's not worth it. You understand?
I'm a cop. Maybe I can help.

84
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:16,566
Okay. I'm fine.

85
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:18,525
-It's just that--
-Listen to me.

86
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:21,406
We'll get through this together.
What's your name?

87
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:22,933
Patience Phillips.

88
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:24,924
But this cat....

89
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:28,609
Sure, sure, Patience,
and it's a real beauty.

90
00:10:29,533 --> 00:10:32,206
-Very cute.
-The cat's not up here any more.

91
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:35,730
Okay. And I'm sure that
makes you very sad.

92
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:38,203
-What's your apartment number?
-Twenty-three!

93
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:39,727
Hold on!

94
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:43,122
Hurry.

95
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:49,532
I got you.

96
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,801
-You okay?
-Thanks.

97
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:03,844
You sure you're okay?

98
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:06,685
That was the cat.

99
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:07,933
You weren't kidding.

100
00:11:07,933 --> 00:11:10,447
You actually climbed out there
to rescue your cat?

101
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:13,333
Yeah. I mean, no.
It's not my cat.  It's a cat.

102
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,164
To rescue somebody else's cat?

103
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:17,610
Well, that's something else.

104
00:11:19,933 --> 00:11:21,810
Oh, my gosh, I'm late for my job!

105
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:26,491
-I'm on a deadline today.
-Yeah? Well, good luck with that.

106
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:27,682
Thanks.

107
00:11:27,733 --> 00:11:29,166
Thank you!

108
00:12:08,773 --> 00:12:11,492
After all, no one can defeat Father Time.

109
00:12:12,373 --> 00:12:15,729
Though you did put up
a hell of a fight, didn't you?

110
00:12:15,973 --> 00:12:19,886
Beau-line works wonders, doesn't it?

111
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:21,572
Yes, it does.

112
00:12:22,573 --> 00:12:24,131
I have a busy day today.

113
00:12:24,373 --> 00:12:27,604
Drinks, then dinner.
Don't wait up, will you, darling?

114
00:12:27,973 --> 00:12:30,973
I stopped waiting
a long time ago, George.

115
00:12:30,973 --> 00:12:33,646
Oh, and that lunch tomorrow?

116
00:12:33,973 --> 00:12:36,885
-Cancel that too, will you?
-Problems?

117
00:12:37,573 --> 00:12:38,773
I doubt it...

118
00:12:38,773 --> 00:12:42,732
...but Slavicky won't stop calling.
You know scientists.

119
00:12:42,973 --> 00:12:47,649
They're worse than models. You have to
coddle them all the time like little children.

120
00:12:47,773 --> 00:12:51,129
I'll have Wesley reschedule. Bye.

121
00:13:09,373 --> 00:13:12,524
Hey! Man sandwich, 12 o'clock.

122
00:13:14,773 --> 00:13:16,252
Oh, my God.

123
00:13:23,173 --> 00:13:24,765
Hello, Miss Phillips.

124
00:13:24,973 --> 00:13:26,406
Hi.

125
00:13:28,573 --> 00:13:32,173
This is the officer I was telling you
about from earlier.

126
00:13:32,173 --> 00:13:33,652
Detective Lone.

127
00:13:35,173 --> 00:13:38,131
-Tom Lone.
-God, that is such a good name.

128
00:13:38,773 --> 00:13:39,973
Tom Lone.

129
00:13:39,973 --> 00:13:43,329
Rhymes with cone, phone, bone.

130
00:13:44,773 --> 00:13:46,923
Not that rhyming's all that important.

131
00:13:48,373 --> 00:13:50,682
I'll just be in my cubicle.

132
00:13:51,373 --> 00:13:52,647
Alone.

133
00:13:57,373 --> 00:13:59,409
-Hi.
-Hi.

134
00:14:00,373 --> 00:14:02,728
How'd you get...?

135
00:14:03,973 --> 00:14:05,173
You dropped something.

136
00:14:05,173 --> 00:14:07,846
You can really cover a lot of ground
when you're in a hurry.

137
00:14:08,173 --> 00:14:09,526
Thanks.

138
00:14:11,173 --> 00:14:12,367
Is this yours?

139
00:14:13,573 --> 00:14:15,086
Yeah.

140
00:14:15,373 --> 00:14:16,573
-It's nice.
-Thanks.

141
00:14:16,573 --> 00:14:19,326
Yeah, it kind of reminds me
of early Chagall.

142
00:14:19,573 --> 00:14:20,892
Elegant, but whimsical.

143
00:14:21,373 --> 00:14:23,173
Very much in the...

144
00:14:23,173 --> 00:14:26,051
-...tradition of the old Dutch Masters.
-I'm impressed.

145
00:14:26,173 --> 00:14:30,610
Don't be. I noticed all the art in your
apartment, so I Googled it at the office.

146
00:14:30,973 --> 00:14:33,726
-No, but really, I like it.
-Thanks.

147
00:14:34,573 --> 00:14:39,010
Listen, I wanted to apologize about this
morning for thinking you were a jumper.

148
00:14:39,373 --> 00:14:41,773
I was hoping to make it up
by taking you to coffee.

149
00:14:41,773 --> 00:14:45,766
I know this great Italian place
around the corner, Grecchio's on 6th.

150
00:14:45,973 --> 00:14:49,443
Or, listen, maybe tomorrow's better.
Say, 1:00?

151
00:14:51,373 --> 00:14:52,567
Yes.

152
00:14:54,973 --> 00:14:56,770
-Okay.
-Yeah?

153
00:14:56,773 --> 00:14:58,491
Okay. So tomorrow then, 1:00.

154
00:14:58,573 --> 00:15:00,803
-You make sure she gets there.
-Yes, officer.

155
00:15:00,973 --> 00:15:03,168
-Counting on you.
-I screw it up...

156
00:15:03,373 --> 00:15:05,329
...you can throw away the key.

157
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:09,131
See you tomorrow.

158
00:15:09,373 --> 00:15:10,886
Okay, bye.

159
00:15:13,573 --> 00:15:14,722
Patience.

160
00:15:14,773 --> 00:15:17,606
-That is a man in serious like with you.
-You think?

161
00:15:18,373 --> 00:15:20,173
-Hello.
-We got a lot of work to do.

162
00:15:20,173 --> 00:15:22,050
First, you gotta shave those legs.

163
00:15:22,573 --> 00:15:25,573
Second, you have to wear that leather outfit
we got you for your birthday.

164
00:15:25,573 --> 00:15:28,849
-Remember?
-First, it's only coffee.

165
00:15:29,173 --> 00:15:34,725
And second, I will never, ever,
ever wear that leather outfit.

166
00:15:51,053 --> 00:15:52,486
Good night!

167
00:15:57,053 --> 00:15:59,203
Hi, this is Patience
in the art department.

168
00:15:59,453 --> 00:16:03,048
Yeah, I'm expecting a messenger
to come and pick up--

169
00:16:03,053 --> 00:16:06,250
But it's gotta be there by midnight.

170
00:16:07,253 --> 00:16:10,450
Well, I....
I know it's not your fault, but....

171
00:16:12,053 --> 00:16:13,452
Okay.

172
00:16:13,853 --> 00:16:15,411
I'll take it myself.

173
00:16:46,253 --> 00:16:48,972
Hello? Is anybody in there?

174
00:16:57,053 --> 00:16:59,123
Oh, come on, Slavicky.

175
00:16:59,453 --> 00:17:01,205
When did you grow a conscience?

176
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:04,643
I don't care that the FDA never saw
the headaches...

177
00:17:04,853 --> 00:17:07,321
...and the nausea
and the fainting spells.

178
00:17:07,853 --> 00:17:10,651
Those are symptoms I can live with.

179
00:17:13,853 --> 00:17:15,206
Hello?

180
00:17:19,253 --> 00:17:23,453
And with what we stand to make
from consumers demanding their fix...

181
00:17:23,453 --> 00:17:25,444
...I can live with it being addictive.

182
00:17:25,853 --> 00:17:28,686
But these side effects
from the long-term studies....

183
00:17:28,853 --> 00:17:32,687
That won't happen if they keep using it.
And we'll make sure they do...

184
00:17:33,053 --> 00:17:35,408
...because that's where
the money comes from.

185
00:17:35,453 --> 00:17:37,205
I'm not sure any more.

186
00:17:40,253 --> 00:17:42,403
Hello? Hello?

187
00:17:54,053 --> 00:17:55,725
I thought I could live with it...

188
00:17:57,653 --> 00:18:00,406
...but I can't live with turning
people into monsters.

189
00:18:01,253 --> 00:18:02,402
Oh, my gosh!

190
00:18:02,453 --> 00:18:06,128
You've gotta let me pull the plug.
We can't let this go on the shelves.

191
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:08,968
Who's there?

192
00:18:10,253 --> 00:18:12,608
-Armando, come in.
-I'm on my way.

193
00:18:33,053 --> 00:18:35,283
You can come out now.
It's okay.

194
00:18:35,453 --> 00:18:37,762
We'd just like to ask you
a few questions.

195
00:18:40,253 --> 00:18:41,368
Sorry.

196
00:18:42,053 --> 00:18:44,886
But I think maybe I'm in the wrong--

197
00:18:46,253 --> 00:18:49,290
-What are you doing?
-Don't ever do that again.

198
00:19:28,853 --> 00:19:30,127
Where is she?

199
00:19:34,853 --> 00:19:37,083
She ran down to waste treatment,
jumped in a pipe.

200
00:19:38,453 --> 00:19:40,648
We don't know who she is,
but we know what she heard.

201
00:19:40,853 --> 00:19:43,686
We can 't risk it.
Get rid of her.

202
00:19:46,253 --> 00:19:47,811
Seal the door.

203
00:25:25,213 --> 00:25:27,602
Patience Phillips,
I've never been so proud of you.

204
00:25:27,613 --> 00:25:30,252
You're probably sipping
your decaf soy whatever right now...

205
00:25:30,613 --> 00:25:33,173
... fantasizing about licking
the foam off his lips.

206
00:25:33,613 --> 00:25:36,013
Wait, that's what I'm doing.
Anway, how'd the presentation go?

207
00:25:36,013 --> 00:25:39,210
Did you get me free samples of it?
Listen, call me.

208
00:25:43,213 --> 00:25:44,612
What...?

209
00:25:49,213 --> 00:25:51,773
Hi, I'll take a decaf latte.

210
00:25:52,213 --> 00:25:55,523
Hey, Patience, it's Tom Lone.
I'm here at Grecchio's waiting...

211
00:25:55,813 --> 00:25:57,849
...and you 're not here.

212
00:25:58,813 --> 00:26:01,646
Anyway, I gotta get back to work, so....

213
00:26:01,813 --> 00:26:03,246
Bye.

214
00:26:18,013 --> 00:26:21,403
Okay, kitty.
It's time for you to go home.

215
00:26:22,813 --> 00:26:23,848
Now....

216
00:26:45,493 --> 00:26:47,165
-Are you Ophelia Powers?
-Y es.

217
00:26:47,293 --> 00:26:50,285
-I got your cat off a ledge and ever since--
-Why, Midnight.

218
00:26:50,293 --> 00:26:53,251
You've never brought a stranger
home before.

219
00:26:53,893 --> 00:26:55,485
PIease, come in.

220
00:26:56,293 --> 00:26:59,683
No, I can't come in.
I've got to go to-- I'm late.

221
00:27:20,893 --> 00:27:22,565
-Midnight.
-I'm sorry?

222
00:27:22,693 --> 00:27:23,967
Her name.

223
00:27:24,493 --> 00:27:29,328
She's an Egyptian Mau,
the rarest of breeds. Temple cats.

224
00:27:29,893 --> 00:27:32,202
It's said that Maus have
special powers.

225
00:27:32,893 --> 00:27:35,009
Like popping out of nowhere? I know.

226
00:27:35,293 --> 00:27:37,011
Among other things.

227
00:27:41,293 --> 00:27:42,612
Your cat....

228
00:27:43,693 --> 00:27:45,092
Socrates!

229
00:27:45,493 --> 00:27:46,687
No caffeine.

230
00:27:48,493 --> 00:27:50,211
It makes him irritable.

231
00:27:50,293 --> 00:27:53,012
You look a little out of sorts yourself,
my dear.

232
00:27:53,893 --> 00:27:55,292
The cats, perhaps.

233
00:27:55,693 --> 00:27:58,693
They seem to be taking quite
an unusual shine to you.

234
00:27:58,693 --> 00:28:01,969
This has been a really bad day
for me already.

235
00:28:02,293 --> 00:28:05,922
-I can't even remember most of yesterday.
-Perhaps I can help you.

236
00:28:06,493 --> 00:28:07,721
Right.

237
00:28:08,293 --> 00:28:11,205
This really isn't your problem.
I don't even know why I'm here.

238
00:28:11,293 --> 00:28:14,893
-It's all right. Tell me, please.
-Really. I'm late for work.

239
00:28:14,893 --> 00:28:18,932
-I'm sorry. I shouldn't even....
-You should come back any time. I'm always here.

240
00:28:29,293 --> 00:28:30,521
Catnip.

241
00:28:37,693 --> 00:28:38,887
No--

242
00:28:45,493 --> 00:28:48,405
I'm fine. I am fine.

243
00:28:49,613 --> 00:28:51,569
What the hell is wrong with you, Phillips?!

244
00:28:52,013 --> 00:28:54,652
You never delivered the design!

245
00:28:55,013 --> 00:28:56,813
You don't even know where they are.

246
00:28:56,813 --> 00:29:01,409
You do not know where they are because,
and I quote you, you "cannot remember"!

247
00:29:01,613 --> 00:29:05,083
Your incompetence is staggering!

248
00:29:08,213 --> 00:29:10,966
Are you even listening to me?

249
00:29:21,413 --> 00:29:22,892
I'm sorry!

250
00:29:24,413 --> 00:29:25,732
"Sorry"?

251
00:29:27,413 --> 00:29:29,210
Sorry's not nearly enough.

252
00:29:29,813 --> 00:29:31,041
Okay.

