Hold on tight. I gotta stop this thing.

497
00:59:53,578 --> 00:59:55,489
-Mom!
-Frankie.

498
00:59:59,578 --> 01:00:01,136
Mom! Mom!

499
01:00:01,378 --> 01:00:03,448
Help, Mom!

500
01:00:04,978 --> 01:00:06,127
Mom!

501
01:00:10,978 --> 01:00:14,015
Help, Mom! Help! Help!

502
01:00:43,378 --> 01:00:46,378
You are one tough little guy.
You know that?

503
01:00:46,378 --> 01:00:48,687
-Take it easy, partner.
-Bye.

504
01:00:52,978 --> 01:00:54,696
It's over.

505
01:00:54,778 --> 01:00:58,134
Well, I'm not sure how you did it,
but I'm impressed.

506
01:00:58,378 --> 01:01:01,609
Well, I saw how you did. And so am I.

507
01:01:01,978 --> 01:01:03,411
-You know what?
-What?

508
01:01:03,778 --> 01:01:07,373
We should celebrate. Why don't you
let me take you to dinner tonight?

509
01:01:07,378 --> 01:01:10,927
I would love to, but I can't.
Not tonight. I've got...

510
01:01:11,578 --> 01:01:15,207
...some business
that I have to take care of.

511
01:02:11,098 --> 01:02:13,658
You picked the wrong house.

512
01:02:16,498 --> 01:02:18,329
You're the cat that killed Slavicky.

513
01:02:18,898 --> 01:02:21,298
You don't believe everything
you see on TV, do you?

514
01:02:21,298 --> 01:02:23,892
-What do you want?
-Your husband. Is he home?

515
01:02:24,298 --> 01:02:26,448
I'm here. Why on earth
would he be home?

516
01:02:26,698 --> 01:02:28,211
Oh, too bad.

517
01:02:33,898 --> 01:02:37,413
If your husband ever comes home,
tell him I know all about Beau-line.

518
01:02:38,098 --> 01:02:41,408
It's disease in a jar.
I wouldn't caulk a sink with it.

519
01:02:41,698 --> 01:02:45,898
-Come on. I've been using it for years.
-It's your funeral.

520
01:02:45,898 --> 01:02:50,016
Because whoever killed Slavicky did it
to keep Beau-line's toxic little secret.

521
01:02:50,098 --> 01:02:53,408
Are you suggesting that my husband
is a murderer?

522
01:02:53,698 --> 01:02:55,654
I'm suggesting that
you tell me where he is.

523
01:02:56,098 --> 01:02:58,612
-So I'll ask him myself.
-I suppose I should be shocked.

524
01:02:59,098 --> 01:03:02,295
Protest his innocence. But the truth is...

525
01:03:03,298 --> 01:03:05,050
...that man's capable of anything.

526
01:03:05,698 --> 01:03:07,370
You wanna find him?

527
01:03:09,298 --> 01:03:10,811
There he is.

528
01:03:15,898 --> 01:03:18,287
-Thanks.
-I'd like to help.

529
01:03:18,898 --> 01:03:20,098
How can I reach you?

530
01:03:20,098 --> 01:03:21,531
I'm not exactly listed.

531
01:03:21,898 --> 01:03:23,456
Take my phone.

532
01:03:57,938 --> 01:04:01,010
Call the cops.
You're not going to believe this.

533
01:04:01,538 --> 01:04:03,574
I think this is a total waste of time.

534
01:04:03,938 --> 01:04:06,247
-Don't.
-What?

535
01:04:06,938 --> 01:04:08,417
Think. Ever.

536
01:04:09,338 --> 01:04:11,977
Consider it a condition
of our relationship.

537
01:04:21,338 --> 01:04:23,727
I love this part.

538
01:04:26,138 --> 01:04:28,732
-Who the hell--?
-Like my nails?

539
01:04:30,338 --> 01:04:32,010
Just got them done.

540
01:04:33,938 --> 01:04:35,212
My bad.

541
01:04:36,938 --> 01:04:38,929
Get your paws off me this instant!

542
01:04:39,338 --> 01:04:41,693
I know about Beau-line,
and your cover-up.

543
01:04:42,338 --> 01:04:43,327
What?

544
01:04:44,138 --> 01:04:46,811
So did my girl, Patience.
That's why you killed her.

545
01:04:47,138 --> 01:04:50,738
-What? I didn't kill her--
-Too bad your last words will be a lie.

546
01:04:50,738 --> 01:04:52,330
Freeze!

547
01:05:15,938 --> 01:05:17,132
Hey!

548
01:05:17,738 --> 01:05:20,491
Hold it right there.
Don't you move.

549
01:05:20,738 --> 01:05:22,888
Now, come down from there
nice and easy.

550
01:05:23,138 --> 01:05:25,936
Cats come when they feel like it.

551
01:05:26,738 --> 01:05:28,330
Not when they're told.

552
01:05:28,538 --> 01:05:31,769
I won't tell you again. You turn around.
Hands on your head.

553
01:05:51,338 --> 01:05:52,737
You're under arrest.

554
01:06:08,138 --> 01:06:09,457
Gotcha!

555
01:06:12,338 --> 01:06:14,738
-You think this is some kind of a game?
-Now we're playing.

556
01:06:14,738 --> 01:06:18,253
-You're playing. I'm at work.
-Seems like you love your job.

557
01:06:21,938 --> 01:06:25,169
-Don't I get din-din first?
-I'll feed you in your cell.

558
01:06:42,938 --> 01:06:45,168
Careful. That cable hits us,
we're both fried.

559
01:06:45,338 --> 01:06:47,568
I knew I felt a spark between us.

560
01:06:53,138 --> 01:06:56,138
-Not on the first date.
-Don't flatter yourself. I'm taken.

561
01:06:56,138 --> 01:06:57,412
Does she know about us?

562
01:06:57,938 --> 01:06:59,212
There's no "us."

563
01:07:00,938 --> 01:07:02,656
Too bad.

564
01:07:06,338 --> 01:07:07,771
It's over.

565
01:07:20,138 --> 01:07:21,457
There she is.

566
01:07:22,538 --> 01:07:23,937
Okay, boys.

567
01:07:24,338 --> 01:07:27,011
Show of hands.
Who can see in the dark?

568
01:07:29,138 --> 01:07:30,127
I can.

569
01:07:38,098 --> 01:07:42,250
But this is a disaster!
It's a total bloody disaster.

570
01:07:44,098 --> 01:07:48,296
How does she know all this?
Who is she, anyway? And how come--?

571
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:50,092
It's all right.

572
01:07:50,698 --> 01:07:52,211
Don't be scared.

573
01:07:54,298 --> 01:07:59,008
Great. You haven't got a clue, do you?
We are in absolute ruin here...

574
01:07:59,098 --> 01:08:02,647
...and your brilliant piece of advice
to me is: "Don't be scared"?

575
01:08:02,698 --> 01:08:06,657
No. My advice to you, George...

576
01:08:07,498 --> 01:08:08,698
...quit the self-tanning.

577
01:08:08,698 --> 01:08:11,098
Stop eating Viagra like they're vitamins.

578
01:08:11,098 --> 01:08:15,808
Resist the urge to date children born the
same day they invented the cell phone.

579
01:08:16,498 --> 01:08:20,127
For once, George,
in your miserable life...

580
01:08:21,298 --> 01:08:22,526
...be a man!

581
01:08:32,698 --> 01:08:33,898
Terrific.

582
01:08:33,898 --> 01:08:36,287
Beau-line works wonders, doesn't it?

583
01:08:36,898 --> 01:08:39,412
Okay, Sal. What do you think?

584
01:08:42,898 --> 01:08:45,776
I don't know. You going to a church
or a Playboy mansion?

585
01:08:45,898 --> 01:08:47,456
Well, that was helpful.

586
01:08:48,298 --> 01:08:50,414
I'm such a freak.

587
01:08:50,698 --> 01:08:54,134
PIease, I'm a freak Thursday
through Sunday, big deal.

588
01:08:54,298 --> 01:08:56,766
Okay, but what if he doesn't like...

589
01:08:57,298 --> 01:09:00,210
-...the real me?
-He can't pick and choose, Patience.

590
01:09:00,298 --> 01:09:03,893
If he wants this to work,
he's gonna have to like all of you.

591
01:09:14,098 --> 01:09:17,215
-Senora Hedare. Perdon.
-Go.

592
01:09:26,098 --> 01:09:27,326
Pretty.

593
01:09:28,498 --> 01:09:30,056
-Thanks.
-Oh, you too.

594
01:09:30,298 --> 01:09:32,448
But I was talking about the fish.

595
01:09:33,898 --> 01:09:35,616
Detective work is like dating.

596
01:09:35,698 --> 01:09:39,452
It's all about the pursuit.
But when you catch them--

597
01:09:44,698 --> 01:09:46,450
You like your sushi, huh?

598
01:09:48,898 --> 01:09:50,331
That's good.

599
01:09:54,898 --> 01:09:57,651
So tell me about this one...

600
01:09:58,498 --> 01:09:59,931
...that got away.

601
01:10:00,298 --> 01:10:01,526
Catwoman.

602
01:10:02,098 --> 01:10:06,569
-You heard of her?
-Oh, yeah. Hot, black leather, whip.

603
01:10:06,898 --> 01:10:08,570
She kissed me.

604
01:10:09,298 --> 01:10:11,493
-Really?
-Yeah.

605
01:10:11,698 --> 01:10:14,690
-What do you think about that?
-Depends.

606
01:10:15,298 --> 01:10:18,290
-You like bad girls?
-Only if they like me back.

607
01:10:21,298 --> 01:10:24,176
No, listen, bad isn't something
that does it for me.

608
01:10:24,298 --> 01:10:27,813
Okay, bad, good.
Gotta be something in between, right?

609
01:10:28,498 --> 01:10:31,251
Maybe it's a little more complicated.

610
01:10:31,498 --> 01:10:34,410
-Why don't we talk about you?
-Okay.

611
01:10:35,098 --> 01:10:38,568
-What's it like to be an artist?
-Well, I'm not really an artist.

612
01:10:38,698 --> 01:10:41,531
I mean, yeah, I did go to art school...

613
01:10:41,698 --> 01:10:45,486
...but then I got a regular job
at an advertising agency...

614
01:10:46,498 --> 01:10:51,936
...and now I don't really know
what I am any more.

615
01:10:54,898 --> 01:10:56,490
Well, I know what you are.

616
01:10:57,898 --> 01:10:59,570
You're different.

617
01:11:00,298 --> 01:11:01,811
You're special.

618
01:11:03,898 --> 01:11:06,298
-And I like that about you.
-Thanks.

619
01:11:06,298 --> 01:11:07,777
No, it's true.

620
01:11:09,898 --> 01:11:11,854
And I want to know more about you.

621
01:11:14,098 --> 01:11:15,087
You know...

622
01:11:15,818 --> 01:11:18,093
...I guess there's a few things
I need to explain.

623
01:11:18,218 --> 01:11:20,812
Like what, your new look? Huh?

624
01:11:21,218 --> 01:11:25,006
-Your dunk shot?
-No, that's not what I was thinking.

625
01:11:25,418 --> 01:11:26,692
Hey.

626
01:11:29,018 --> 01:11:30,770
You can tell me anything.

627
01:11:38,018 --> 01:11:39,815
I'm....

628
01:11:48,818 --> 01:11:50,410
I hate the rain!

629
01:12:00,818 --> 01:12:02,456
What were you saying?

630
01:12:05,018 --> 01:12:06,815
Nothing important.

631
01:13:37,418 --> 01:13:38,771
Tom?

632
01:13:47,018 --> 01:13:48,417
It's me.

633
01:13:49,418 --> 01:13:51,409
You were right about Beau-line's secrets.

634
01:13:51,818 --> 01:13:56,016
I can 't believe it, but you were right.
Beau-line is toxic.

635
01:13:56,018 --> 01:14:00,216
I have proof. We can stop him,
but we have to stop him together.

636
01:14:00,218 --> 01:14:04,097
George will be launching Beau-line
at a press conference tomorrow.

637
01:14:04,418 --> 01:14:06,978
Beau-line will be on the shelves
on Monday.

638
01:14:54,938 --> 01:14:56,132
So, what'd you find?

639
01:14:56,138 --> 01:15:00,495
Enough evidence to put someone away
for a long, long time.

640
01:15:01,538 --> 01:15:04,530
I was everything they wanted me to be.

641
01:15:05,138 --> 01:15:07,857
I was never more beautiful.

642
01:15:08,138 --> 01:15:10,015
Never more powerful.

643
01:15:10,538 --> 01:15:14,133
And then I turned 40
and they threw me away.

644
01:15:17,138 --> 01:15:19,493
It's all there behind the desk.

645
01:15:33,338 --> 01:15:34,657
How'd I do?

646
01:15:35,138 --> 01:15:39,256
The clawed-flesh thing
was a little tricky...

647
01:15:39,338 --> 01:15:41,249
...but I think I pulled it off.

648
01:15:45,938 --> 01:15:49,248
-You killed him?
-No one is gonna stop Beau-line...

649
01:15:49,538 --> 01:15:51,335
...from hitting the shelves.

650
01:15:51,338 --> 01:15:52,851
Not Slavicky.

651
01:15:53,738 --> 01:15:57,333
Not George. And certainly not you.

652
01:15:58,538 --> 01:16:01,336
I'm sorry. I'm forgetting my manners.

653
01:16:01,538 --> 01:16:03,338
Can I offer you something?

654
01:16:03,338 --> 01:16:05,215
Can of tuna? Saucer of milk?

655
01:16:06,338 --> 01:16:11,935
Smoking gun? Which, sweetheart, you
just emptied into my husband's chest.

656
01:16:15,338 --> 01:16:17,329
Oh, George!

657
01:16:17,738 --> 01:16:21,970
Help, somebody help!
It's Catwoman! She killed George.

658
01:16:23,138 --> 01:16:24,810
Oh, my God!

659
01:17:35,338 --> 01:17:36,771
Patience.

660
01:17:44,338 --> 01:17:45,851
I'm sorry.

661
01:17:52,138 --> 01:17:55,733
I guess you could take this right
out of my hands if you wanted.

662
01:18:00,538 --> 01:18:01,971
If I wanted.

663
01:18:10,738 --> 01:18:14,333
I'm telling you.
Slavicky had evidence that Beau-line was toxic.

664
01:18:14,938 --> 01:18:16,610
That's why Laurel killed him.

665
01:18:16,738 --> 01:18:20,174
George found out and she killed him too.
She was covering it up.

666
01:18:20,338 --> 01:18:23,853
Ballistics show the same weapon killed both men: the gun that was in your hand.

667
01:18:23,938 --> 01:18:27,010
-Catwoman's hand.
-What's the difference?

668
01:18:28,738 --> 01:18:31,855
-Guess it doesn't matter.
-Don't you understand?

669
01:18:32,338 --> 01:18:36,172
All of the evidence, every single piece,
it points to you.

670
01:18:36,538 --> 01:18:38,927
There's nothing that shows me
anything else.

671
01:18:40,138 --> 01:18:41,491
There's me.

672
01:18:42,538 --> 01:18:44,290
You can believe me.

673
01:18:50,938 --> 01:18:53,498
Do you remember the first time
you saw me?

674
01:18:54,538 --> 01:18:55,687
Yeah.

675
01:18:56,338 --> 01:18:57,976
What did you see?

676
01:18:58,138 --> 01:18:59,412
A girl...

677
01:18:59,938 --> 01:19:01,417
...rescuing a cat.

678
01:19:01,738 --> 01:19:03,091
No, you didn't.

679
01:19:04,138 --> 01:19:08,370
You saw a crazy person out on a ledge
trying to jump.

680
01:19:10,138 --> 01:19:14,495
And all the evidence pointed to that,
didn't it?

681
01:19:14,938 --> 01:19:17,498
I really need you to believe me.

682
01:19:22,138 --> 01:19:23,651
How can I?

683
01:19:25,138 --> 01:19:26,969
I don't know who you are.

684
01:19:31,738 --> 01:19:34,536
I'm the same girl
you were with last night.

685
01:19:51,538 --> 01:19:53,176
Take her back.

686
01:20:06,538 --> 01:20:08,210
You be a nice kitty, now.

687
01:20:31,738 --> 01:20:33,490
Look at it this way, Lone.

688
01:20:34,138 --> 01:20:37,335
You may have lost your woman,
but at least you got your man.

689
01:20:39,538 --> 01:20:40,766
Did I?

690
01:20:41,338 --> 01:20:42,487
Yeah.

691
01:20:48,098 --> 01:20:49,850
Hello, Midnight.

692
01:21:09,098 --> 01:21:11,293
You've spent a lifetime caged.

693
01:21:11,498 --> 01:21:15,616
By accepting who you are,
all of who you are...

694
01:21:16,298 --> 01:21:17,777
... you can be free.

695
01:21:18,098 --> 01:21:19,816
And freedom is power.

696
01:21:22,898 --> 01:21:25,128
It's not just about me any more, Midnight.

697
01:21:35,498 --> 01:21:36,897
You know...

698
01:21:37,298 --> 01:21:40,131
... Lassie would have brought me a key.

699
01:21:40,898 --> 01:21:42,570
Cross your paws.

700
01:22:10,298 --> 01:22:13,290
-We're gonna shift-change in half an hour.
-All right.

701
01:22:16,298 --> 01:22:19,051
-Dave's gonna take over then?
-Yeah, as far as I know.

702
01:22:19,298 --> 01:22:21,129
Yeah, right through here, pal.

703
01:22:22,298 --> 01:22:24,528
You'll get to talk to a lawyer.

704
01:22:44,498 --> 01:22:45,647
Are you okay?

705
01:22:45,698 --> 01:22:48,496
A girl like me lands on her feet.

706
01:22:49,898 --> 01:22:51,809
Wait! Wait!

707
01:23:01,578 --> 01:23:03,773
My husband dreamed of a world...

708
01:23:03,978 --> 01:23:07,288
...where every woman could be
as beautiful as she wanted to be.

709
01:23:08,178 --> 01:23:13,578
He dedicated his life pursuing that dream.
As Hedare's new chief executive...

710
01:23:13,578 --> 01:23:16,650
...I intend to make that dream a reality...

711
01:23:17,178 --> 01:23:21,888
...by proceeding with tomorrow's launch of Beau-line.

712
01:23:28,578 --> 01:23:29,897
Thank you!

713
01:23:33,978 --> 01:23:38,017
Thank you so much. I have been dying
to get some of this stuff.

714
01:23:38,178 --> 01:23:42,330
My husband would have wanted you to have it.
He wanted that for everyone.

715
01:23:44,178 --> 01:23:47,409
-Detective Lone. What a surprise.
-Yeah?

716
01:23:47,778 --> 01:23:53,057
Everyone, this is the man that brought
my husband's killer to justice.

717
01:23:56,178 --> 01:23:57,930
Can I talk to you for a minute, in private?

718
01:23:57,978 --> 01:24:00,208
Come upstairs to my office.

719
01:24:08,778 --> 01:24:11,178
-Number five, ready to go.
-Yeah, yeah.

720
01:24:11,178 --> 01:24:13,294
Yeah, go ahead. Right there.

721
01:24:22,578 --> 01:24:25,012
Get a move on.
Gotta meet that midnight delivery.

722
01:25:01,618 --> 01:25:04,618
I saw her standing over him.
There were claw marks all over his body.

723
01:25:04,618 --> 01:25:07,371
-But not on Slavicky's.
-Because she didn't have the time.

724
01:25:07,618 --> 01:25:09,574
She also didn't have a motive.

725
01:25:11,218 --> 01:25:13,812
-I don't know.
-What if I told you I know the truth?

726
01:25:14,218 --> 01:25:16,937
That I know who killed your husband,
I know about Beau-line.

727
01:25:17,218 --> 01:25:20,574
Why, detective, you make it sound
like I'm a suspect.

728
01:25:21,418 --> 01:25:23,932
What if I told you I had evidence?

729
01:25:25,618 --> 01:25:29,818
If you have evidence,
then how come I'm not in cuffs?

730
01:25:29,818 --> 01:25:33,936
Well, you're a smart woman,
Mrs. Hedare. Beautiful. Rich.

731
01:25:34,618 --> 01:25:36,688
I thought maybe we could
work something out.

732
01:25:37,018 --> 01:25:42,046
So this evidence.... You'll make it
disappear? Pin it on the other girl?

733
01:25:42,418 --> 01:25:44,648
If that's what you want me to do.

734
01:25:45,418 --> 01:25:46,618
And you?

735
01:25:46,618 --> 01:25:49,530
-What do you want?
-You just gave me what I want.

736
01:25:49,618 --> 01:25:51,495
You just told me it was you.

737
01:25:52,618 --> 01:25:55,291
Now, why would you believe it was me?

738
01:25:56,818 --> 01:25:58,376
Because I finally trusted a friend.

739
01:25:58,618 --> 01:26:01,132
Yeah, well, your friend
just got you killed.

740
01:26:02,818 --> 01:26:05,776
Don't be stupid, Laurel.
You don't want to kill a cop.

741
01:26:06,418 --> 01:26:08,374
I'm a woman, Lone.

742
01:26:09,418 --> 01:26:12,808
I'm used to doing all kinds
of things I don't wanna do.

743
01:26:13,018 --> 01:26:15,088
Give my regards to my husband.

744
01:26:21,418 --> 01:26:22,976
How sweet.

745
01:26:23,218 --> 01:26:25,686
Thanks. Now I can kill you both.

746
01:26:44,818 --> 01:26:46,809
Hold on, I gotta stop.

747
01:26:48,418 --> 01:26:49,612
How is it?

748
01:26:49,618 --> 01:26:51,495
Well, there goes my jump shot.

749
01:26:52,018 --> 01:26:53,167
Listen.

750
01:26:53,218 --> 01:26:55,288
I want you to know I'm sorry.

751
01:26:55,618 --> 01:26:57,813
I should have trusted you all along.

752
01:26:58,018 --> 01:27:00,612
You're confusing me
with somebody else.

753
01:27:01,618 --> 01:27:03,256
Come on, Patience.

754
01:27:08,818 --> 01:27:10,092
I'll take this side.

755
01:28:06,218 --> 01:28:08,686
I can't believe I ever trusted you.

756
01:28:09,218 --> 01:28:12,369
-You're a fake.
-And what are you? A hero?

757
01:28:14,618 --> 01:28:15,971
A thief?

758
01:28:17,618 --> 01:28:19,017
A freak?

759
01:28:23,618 --> 01:28:27,008
If you don't have an identity,
why keep it a secret?

760
01:28:27,818 --> 01:28:30,252
Because you killed me.

761
01:28:35,018 --> 01:28:37,896
It was me you flushed down the pipes.

762
01:28:41,018 --> 01:28:42,736
I'm Patience Phillips.

763
01:28:44,018 --> 01:28:45,610
That's who's under there?

764
01:29:17,018 --> 01:29:18,974
-I can't be hurt.
-Beau-line.

765
01:29:19,418 --> 01:29:22,649
You stop using it
and your face disintegrates.

766
01:29:26,618 --> 01:29:30,691
And if you keep using it,
skin like living marble.

767
01:29:36,818 --> 01:29:38,888
And you can't feel a thing.

768
01:30:09,818 --> 01:30:13,208
You're just a scared little girl
playing dress-up.

769
01:30:17,618 --> 01:30:19,848
Nobody. Nothing.

770
01:30:26,018 --> 01:30:28,054
Where do you think you're going?

771
01:30:30,818 --> 01:30:33,013
You're gonna look like a cop-killer.

772
01:30:33,218 --> 01:30:37,530
You wanted to save him.
Honey, you couldn't save yourself.

773
01:30:51,818 --> 01:30:53,171
Game over.

774
01:30:54,218 --> 01:30:55,571
Guess what.

775
01:30:56,618 --> 01:30:58,654
It's overtime.

776
01:31:41,618 --> 01:31:43,051
Give me your hand!

777
01:31:45,818 --> 01:31:47,046
Help me!

778
01:32:15,818 --> 01:32:20,016
I might not be a hero,
but I'm certainly not a killer.

779
01:32:23,618 --> 01:32:24,937
You know...

780
01:32:25,418 --> 01:32:27,170
...once Laurel's boys start talking...

781
01:32:27,818 --> 01:32:30,491
...we'll be able to wrap up
these murder cases pretty easy.

782
01:32:32,018 --> 01:32:35,374
And if Patience is back in her cell
by tomorrow morning...

783
01:32:36,218 --> 01:32:39,176
...it'll be awfully tough to prove
that she was Catwoman.

784
01:32:41,618 --> 01:32:43,131
Exactly.

785
01:33:11,538 --> 01:33:13,654
Delicious, thank you.

786
01:33:14,538 --> 01:33:16,768
You know, the strawberry was good too.

787
01:33:27,138 --> 01:33:29,652
The day I died
was the day I started to live.

788
01:33:31,938 --> 01:33:35,538
In my old life, I longed for someone
to see what was special in me.

789
01:33:35,538 --> 01:33:40,009
You did, and for that
you 'll always be in my heart.

790
01:33:40,338 --> 01:33:43,296
But what I really needed
was for me to see it.

791
01:33:43,938 --> 01:33:45,496
And now I do.

792
01:33:45,738 --> 01:33:47,251
You 're a good man, Tom.

793
01:33:47,538 --> 01:33:51,738
But you live in a world that has no place
for someone like me.

794
01:33:51,738 --> 01:33:55,208
You see, sometimes I'm good.
Oh, I'm very good.

795
01:33:55,338 --> 01:33:59,047
But sometimes I'm bad.
But only as bad as I wanna be.

796
01:33:59,538 --> 01:34:01,017
Freedom is power.

797
01:34:01,338 --> 01:34:06,696
To live a life untamed and unafraid
is the gift that I've been given...

798
01:34:06,738 --> 01:34:09,889
...and so my journey begins.

